rge body of sociological work on the state, civil society, and ethnicity to present an overview of the construction and deconstruction of the secular-Zionist national identity. He shows how Israeliness is becoming a prefix for other identities as well as a legal and political concept of citizen rights granted by the state, though not necessarily equally to different segments of society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aIsraéliens. 0aJewsxIdentityxIsrael. 0aJewszIsraelxIdentity. 0aJuifsxIdentitéxIsraël. 0aNational characteristics, Israeli. 0aReligion and statexIsrael. 0aReligion and statezIsrael. 0aReligion et ÉtatxIsraël. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520939301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520939301.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles